    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-04-24T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-04-24T00:00:00-05:00" n="220" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d220">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Baker</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Gresham</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">San
                                        Jose</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-04-24">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 24,
                                1895</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The minister for foreign affairs of Nicaragua telegraphs me three British
                            vessels are at Corinto to collect indemnity, which Nicaragua can not
                            pay. Great Britain refused postponement or arbitration.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Baker.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
